    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of Toona ciliata, a mahogany (not really cedar) of India, southeast Asia, and Australia. It is similar to Spanish cedar but is redder in color, harder, and heavier.</Note_Text>
